                    <comment id="13060610" author="mikemccand" created="Wed, 6 Jul 2011 15:40:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Initial patch w/ some nocommits still but tests pass...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13060619" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 6 Jul 2011 15:58:21 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think FastBitSet should still have &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
  /** Expert: returns the &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt;[] storing the bits */
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt;[] getBits() { &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; bits; }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The whole reason I had to create OpenBitSet in the first place was that you couldn&apos;t do anything custom fast (on a word-for-word basis) because the bits were locked away from you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13060668" author="mikemccand" created="Wed, 6 Jul 2011 17:24:21 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;OK I&apos;ll add getBits().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13062175" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 8 Jul 2011 21:55:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;New patch, renaming to FixedBitSet, adding test (adapted from TestOBS&apos;s), adding getBits, hashCode, equals.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s ready to commit!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
